    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-15T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="789"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/604</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-15T12:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1918, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 16, 12.23
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1952. Council of Ministers decided last night to take temporary possession of
                    seven German vessels refugeed in Spanish ports, as follows: <hi rend="italic"
                        >Eriphia, Euphemia, Oldenburg, Klio, Mathilde</hi>, [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Siegfried</hi>], <hi rend="italic">Rudolf</hi>. Total tonnage approximately
                    21,000. This decision was arrived at after prolonged and friendly negotiations
                    with Germany, and in said decision Germany has apparently acquiesced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
